1
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:38,300
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,490 --> 00:01:41,229
[Episode 21]

3
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:42,870
I didn't expect

4
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:45,600
these few years abroad to pass so quickly.

5
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:48,800
Ning is about to become
the orchestra's principal cellist.

6
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,460
Chen Fan has also followed her here.

7
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:53,900
While Mengmeng and Zhao Zhenghao
chose to stay back home.

8
00:01:54,039 --> 00:01:54,660
Oh, right.

9
00:01:54,789 --> 00:01:57,310
Xiaole and I,
for our own better development,

10
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:59,310
still chose to go our separate ways.

11
00:02:24,730 --> 00:02:25,900
Chen Fan, Ning.

12
00:02:26,940 --> 00:02:27,820
Stay with her.

13
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,660
I'm going to the restroom.

14
00:02:28,660 --> 00:02:29,660
Okay, be careful.

15
00:02:32,380 --> 00:02:33,280
What's wrong with Ning?

16
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,880
She doesn't look very happy.

17
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:36,590
She...

18
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:38,320
was supposed to become
the principal cellist

19
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,579
after this tour ended.

20
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:42,460
But someone came out of nowhere
and took her spot.

21
00:02:42,460 --> 00:02:43,440
Because of this,

22
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:46,620
she even had an argument
with the conductor.

23
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,840
She's been waiting for this opportunity
for a long time.

24
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,680
But I've seen some media reports.

25
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,210
Her performance was pretty good, right?

26
00:02:55,210 --> 00:02:57,610
That's why they say life is unpredictable.

27
00:03:07,190 --> 00:03:08,090
What's wrong with you?

28
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:10,010
You don't seem in a great mood either.

29
00:03:10,010 --> 00:03:12,410
You haven't released a song
for a long time.

30
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:15,770
She drinks every day,

31
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,579
so I'm not in the mood to write songs.

32
00:03:17,579 --> 00:03:18,400
And my parents

33
00:03:18,430 --> 00:03:19,829
keep urging me to go back.

34
00:03:20,130 --> 00:03:22,590
I've been here
accompanying her for 4 years.

35
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,890
So what are your thoughts?

36
00:03:25,550 --> 00:03:26,680
Why don't you

37
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:27,950
start your own orchestra

38
00:03:27,950 --> 00:03:29,950
and make her the principal cellist?

39
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:31,670
That's exactly what I thought.

40
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:32,660
But whatever I think,

41
00:03:32,660 --> 00:03:34,320
it depends on what she thinks.

42
00:03:35,829 --> 00:03:36,770
In short,

43
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:38,880
as long as she stays,

44
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:39,700
I stay.

45
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,640
You two are such a lovely couple.

46
00:03:42,910 --> 00:03:44,970
You're still as good to her as always.

47
00:03:45,170 --> 00:03:46,800
Isn't that how it should be?

48
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:53,780
What about you?

49
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,510
Still working odd jobs constantly?

50
00:03:55,510 --> 00:03:56,260
Actually, if you have any difficulties,

51
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:56,980
you can just

52
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,000
tell me directly.

53
00:03:59,870 --> 00:04:01,380
I've already quit my job.

54
00:04:01,410 --> 00:04:02,390
Starting tomorrow,

55
00:04:02,390 --> 00:04:03,900
I'll focus on practicing the cello.

56
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:04,640
Don't worry.

57
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:09,970
Luckily, I got into the same school

58
00:04:09,970 --> 00:04:11,280
as Ning back then.

59
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:13,130
Now I have you two to keep me company.

60
00:04:13,130 --> 00:04:13,790
It's great.

61
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:20,110
What about Xiaole?

62
00:04:23,050 --> 00:04:24,560
You grew up together.

63
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:26,210
You haven't been in touch for over a year.

64
00:04:26,210 --> 00:04:27,410
Is that really necessary?

65
00:04:27,410 --> 00:04:29,010
You're not friends anymore?

66
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:35,700
If you ask me,

67
00:04:35,730 --> 00:04:37,730
Xiaole's life hasn't been easy either.

68
00:04:37,730 --> 00:04:39,050
His work environment is unstable.

69
00:04:39,050 --> 00:04:40,650
He always runs around alone.

70
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:41,920
When he works non-stop,

71
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,490
even I can't reach him.

72
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,320
I think

73
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,320
he really needs someone

74
00:04:47,340 --> 00:04:48,400
to be there for him.

75
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:50,420
And look at his dad.

76
00:04:50,890 --> 00:04:52,010
He's been in rehab.

77
00:04:52,450 --> 00:04:53,690
If anything goes wrong,

78
00:04:53,690 --> 00:04:55,080
he has to drop everything he's doing

79
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,080
and go back to him.

80
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:58,600
I think

81
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:00,480
he cares about so many things,

82
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,950
so sometimes, he probably doesn't know

83
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:02,950
what to do either.

84
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:10,670
Ning.

85
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:12,220
The tour is finally over.

86
00:05:12,220 --> 00:05:13,050
Finally,

87
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,010
I can relax a bit.

88
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:15,270
Celebratory drinks.

89
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:17,170
Such a great performance

90
00:05:17,170 --> 00:05:19,170
deserves a proper celebration.

91
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:21,120
I'll definitely come next time.

92
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,800
Alright, alright.

93
00:05:23,010 --> 00:05:23,670
Maybe

94
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:25,160
there won't be a next time.

95
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,610
In the past,

96
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,330
I always felt as long as I worked hard,

97
00:05:32,820 --> 00:05:34,570
everything would pay off.

98
00:05:34,690 --> 00:05:35,650
Whether it was studying

99
00:05:35,650 --> 00:05:36,850
or playing the cello.

100
00:05:38,010 --> 00:05:39,080
But now,

101
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:39,980
I'm not sure.

102
00:05:40,350 --> 00:05:42,340
I feel no matter how hard I try,

103
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:44,830
there will always be someone
better than me.

104
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,800
There are many outstanding people,

105
00:05:48,130 --> 00:05:49,610
but there is only one Ning.

106
00:05:50,310 --> 00:05:50,950
At least,

107
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,980
your love for the cello

108
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:54,270
is beyond doubt.

109
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,570
Maybe.

110
00:05:57,820 --> 00:05:58,950
I'm not sure either.

111
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:00,500
Maybe it's an obsession.

112
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,060
Forget about obsessions.

113
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:03,180
Happiness is what matters most.

114
00:06:03,180 --> 00:06:03,980
To happiness.

115
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:05,050
To happiness.

116
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:09,320
This song is too slow.

117
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:10,320
I'll go change it.

118
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:14,330
Tell me,

119
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,360
how did she manage

120
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:17,740
to stay the same

121
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:19,030
after all these years?

122
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,210
Senior Mark.

123
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:51,070
Can it be fixed within 3 days?

124
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:52,230
Even a miracle worker

125
00:06:52,230 --> 00:06:52,960
couldn't...

126
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:54,590
fix it.

127
00:06:55,510 --> 00:06:56,070
Then...

128
00:06:57,430 --> 00:06:58,630
how much will it cost?

129
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,330
3,000 euros.

130
00:07:03,850 --> 00:07:04,780
That expensive?

131
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,560
I'll pay you a deposit first.

132
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:07,680
No need for that.

133
00:07:08,510 --> 00:07:10,360
I was your senior in high school,

134
00:07:10,390 --> 00:07:12,250
and we're from the same hometown.

135
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:13,630
As for the money,

136
00:07:13,650 --> 00:07:14,980
you don't need to give it to me.

137
00:07:14,980 --> 00:07:15,650
Just treat me to a meal.

138
00:07:15,650 --> 00:07:16,470
That'll be enough.

139
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:17,450
No, no, no.

140
00:07:17,530 --> 00:07:18,680
You've helped me so much already.

141
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,130
I can't take advantage of you again.

142
00:07:20,130 --> 00:07:22,040
I'll definitely pay you the full amount.

143
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:24,570
You won't even give me a chance
to impress you.

144
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:25,670
Do you usually starve yourself?

145
00:07:25,670 --> 00:07:26,730
Why are you so thin?

146
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,580
Is it really that serious?

147
00:07:28,580 --> 00:07:29,910
I'll get you some bread.

148
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:31,420
No need.

149
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:41,200
Life as an international student
is so tough.

150
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,630
I just paid the rent,

151
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:44,380
and I'm completely broke now.

152
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:45,360
If I had known,

153
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,560
I shouldn't have quit my part-time job.

154
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:57,790
[Practicing the cello makes me happy]

155
00:08:01,530 --> 00:08:04,430
[Practicing the cello makes me happy]

156
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:21,080
I have a part-time job opportunity here.

157
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,840
It requires 3 days
of local guiding and interpretation.

158
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:23,880
Food, lodging, and travel are covered.

159
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,140
The pay is 30,000 yuan.

160
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,380
Are you interested?

161
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,980
Share the WeChat account with me.

162
00:09:40,950 --> 00:09:41,590
Why...

163
00:09:42,180 --> 00:09:43,760
are you... here?

164
00:09:44,830 --> 00:09:45,890
Photography work.

165
00:09:46,010 --> 00:09:46,940
Why are you here?

166
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,030
Me?

167
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:50,190
♪ A race of wind and waves ♪

168
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:50,020
H-Haven't I... always been here?

169
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:53,390
♪ The coastline no longer waits ♪

170
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:56,390
♪ Too late to confess ♪

171
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:59,360
♪ The future has fallen through ♪

172
00:10:01,180 --> 00:10:02,410
Wait a second.

173
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:03,300
♪ At least ♪

174
00:10:05,090 --> 00:10:05,750
Well,

175
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:09,240
♪ There's still hope ♪

176
00:10:05,890 --> 00:10:07,870
I've booked the car and lodging.

177
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,700
You should at least pay the rest.

178
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,980
♪ The dresser has lost its light ♪

179
00:10:15,050 --> 00:10:17,850
♪ No hues in sight for a decade ♪

180
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:21,000
♪ The renovated old platform ♪

181
00:10:21,490 --> 00:10:24,280
♪ Who's waiting after turning the page? ♪

182
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:26,810
If he's not answering your call,

183
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:28,060
♪ I shouldn't have ♪

184
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,640
why don't you lend it to me first?

185
00:10:30,290 --> 00:10:33,820
♪ Parted ways with her ♪

186
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,060
How... How many days are you staying?

187
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:34,910
Three days.

188
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:40,390
♪ Fatigued, alone in the dark ♪

189
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:35,830
Where are you staying?

190
00:10:35,830 --> 00:10:36,890
Have you booked it?

191
00:10:37,030 --> 00:10:37,620
No.

192
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,300
Why?

193
00:10:39,590 --> 00:10:40,370
I have a car.

194
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:41,950
I can also help you book a hotel.

195
00:10:40,970 --> 00:10:42,330
♪ Waiting ♪

196
00:10:42,660 --> 00:10:46,560
♪ It's never sunlight ♪

197
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:44,310
No need.

198
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:46,580
Can I borrow your phone for a moment?

199
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:48,030
I can lend you my phone,

200
00:10:47,050 --> 00:10:49,600
♪ When I turn around ♪

201
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:50,270
but you have to let me
make the arrangements.

202
00:10:50,270 --> 00:10:52,820
♪ The story begins ♪

203
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:53,410
What is our relationship now?

204
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:55,720
♪ Without a trace ♪

205
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:54,970
Why should I help you?

206
00:10:57,140 --> 00:10:57,780
We...

207
00:10:58,430 --> 00:10:59,770
can be client and provider.

208
00:10:59,670 --> 00:11:04,480
♪ Later I became a bird, searching ♪

209
00:11:01,610 --> 00:11:03,470
Then it's even more unnecessary.

210
00:11:03,990 --> 00:11:05,450
If you won't lend me your phone,

211
00:11:05,450 --> 00:11:07,180
I'll go find a public phone.

212
00:11:05,690 --> 00:11:08,010
♪ Flying forward all alone ♪

213
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:10,970
♪ Self-comfort is inevitable ♪

214
00:11:10,890 --> 00:11:12,190
We are in a foreign country.

215
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:14,730
♪ Forgive me for not giving up yet ♪

216
00:11:12,370 --> 00:11:14,370
You can't just leave me in the lurch.

217
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:17,020
Not only do I want
to leave you in the lurch,

218
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:17,340
♪ I won't give up ♪

219
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:18,770
I also want to tell your dad

220
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:23,290
♪ Choosing an answer,
repeating the ending a few times ♪

221
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,270
that his daughter has never contacted me.

222
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:22,930
And she gave me the silent treatment
to break up.

223
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:24,780
I can also tell my dad that you gave me

224
00:11:24,140 --> 00:11:28,890
♪ I fly in the crowd
with my nest branches ♪

225
00:11:24,810 --> 00:11:25,770
the silent treatment to break up.

226
00:11:25,770 --> 00:11:27,230
Let's see who he believes.

227
00:11:28,620 --> 00:11:30,240
So that's why you broke up with me?

228
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,660
♪ Watching them ♪

229
00:11:31,770 --> 00:11:36,260
♪ Come and go as the seasons change ♪

230
00:11:32,940 --> 00:11:34,600
I don't want to argue with you.

231
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:39,460
♪ But I still can't do it ♪

232
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:41,930
♪ I can't ♪

233
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:42,620
Do you have a driver's license?

234
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:49,310
♪ Follow in the footsteps of the monsoon ♪

235
00:11:44,290 --> 00:11:44,980
No.

236
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,190
But I can be on call 24/7

237
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:48,050
whenever you need me.

238
00:11:48,050 --> 00:11:49,550
And I know this area very well.

239
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:51,610
I can take you wherever you want to go.

240
00:11:55,730 --> 00:11:56,660
Name your price.

241
00:11:58,020 --> 00:11:58,750
30,000 yuan.

242
00:11:58,970 --> 00:11:59,810
20,000 yuan.

243
00:11:59,890 --> 00:12:00,620
25,000 yuan.

244
00:12:00,620 --> 00:12:01,270
No way.

245
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:02,490
I also need to work part-time as a driver.

246
00:12:02,490 --> 00:12:03,220
20,000 yuan.

247
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:05,370
Fine.

248
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:10,010
Pay first.

249
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,500
I don't have internet access.

250
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:16,260
I'll share my mobile hotspot with you.

251
00:12:21,380 --> 00:12:22,980
The password is my birthday.

252
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:29,480
I've transferred it.

253
00:12:29,650 --> 00:12:30,950
Why only 15,000 yuan?

254
00:12:31,070 --> 00:12:33,250
What if you take the money and run?

255
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:40,900
Welcome.

256
00:12:43,290 --> 00:12:44,620
Let me help you with your luggage.

257
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:45,820
The car is over there.

258
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:48,990
Be careful.

259
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:50,600
The photography equipment inside
is very expensive.

260
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:53,200
A local guide
making the client drive himself—

261
00:12:53,350 --> 00:12:55,010
that's really a first for me.

262
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,020
Well, you're seeing it today.

263
00:12:58,490 --> 00:13:00,230
You've been abroad for so many years.

264
00:13:00,230 --> 00:13:02,690
How come you still
haven't learned to drive?

265
00:13:03,420 --> 00:13:05,150
I never had the chance to learn.

266
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:09,350
Why did you want to be a local guide?

267
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:11,690
Just working.

268
00:13:11,710 --> 00:13:12,600
Making money.

269
00:13:15,610 --> 00:13:17,140
Did you come alone?

270
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:18,060
Where is Ma?

271
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:20,010
Look at my gear.

272
00:13:20,030 --> 00:13:21,760
Does it look like I came with Ma?

273
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:30,010
The intersection ahead.

274
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:30,680
We're almost there.

275
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:31,040
Okay.

276
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:34,680
Almost there.

277
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:36,260
It's just up ahead.

278
00:13:36,510 --> 00:13:37,600
This place you found

279
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:38,840
is quite remote.

280
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,510
We've been walking...

281
00:13:40,510 --> 00:13:41,380
for over 10 minutes,

282
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:42,840
and we're still not there.

283
00:13:43,050 --> 00:13:44,580
We'll be there once we go up.

284
00:13:45,220 --> 00:13:46,330
Need my help?

285
00:13:46,420 --> 00:13:47,450
No, thanks.

286
00:13:59,570 --> 00:14:00,670
You just...

287
00:14:01,490 --> 00:14:02,480
rest first.

288
00:14:05,150 --> 00:14:05,850
I'm hungry.

289
00:14:07,910 --> 00:14:08,620
What do you want to eat?

290
00:14:08,620 --> 00:14:09,820
I'll go buy it for you.

291
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:11,440
How about

292
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:14,000
you get some ingredients and cook for me?

293
00:14:14,110 --> 00:14:15,970
After all, it's my first day here.

294
00:14:15,970 --> 00:14:18,270
If I get an upset stomach
from not adjusting

295
00:14:18,270 --> 00:14:19,600
to the new environment,

296
00:14:20,010 --> 00:14:21,610
it'll delay the photography work.

297
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:22,120
Right?

298
00:14:24,090 --> 00:14:25,860
Then give me the money first.

299
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:28,300
I don't know the prices around here.

300
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,810
Why don't you buy them first

301
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:32,480
and then I'll reimburse you?

302
00:14:33,070 --> 00:14:34,730
Remember to get the receipts.

303
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:36,980
I'm going to get some rest.

304
00:14:38,020 --> 00:14:38,820
You know

305
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:39,850
what I want to eat.

306
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:10,590
Please enjoy.

307
00:15:21,330 --> 00:15:22,660
The plating

308
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:23,700
is pretty good.

309
00:15:30,610 --> 00:15:32,390
The toast isn't burnt?

310
00:15:33,890 --> 00:15:35,420
Did you make this yourself?

311
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:39,100
Are you going to eat or not?

312
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:40,250
I'll eat.

313
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,370
This place you found

314
00:15:51,370 --> 00:15:52,500
is quite beautiful.

315
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:55,180
I really should have come earlier.

316
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:05,860
This stove

317
00:16:05,990 --> 00:16:07,910
has quite a unique shape.

318
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:10,430
The firewood inside—

319
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:11,480
was it all...

320
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:12,290
chopped...

321
00:16:12,710 --> 00:16:13,520
by you?

322
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:18,610
I'm just a local guide.

323
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:20,740
A local guide has no obligation

324
00:16:20,740 --> 00:16:22,740
to explain these things to clients?

325
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:25,980
It came with the apartment.

326
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:35,460
The owner of this musical instrument store

327
00:16:35,460 --> 00:16:37,170
went to the same high school as us.

328
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:38,770
He was a few years ahead of us.

329
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,600
He's a man.

330
00:16:41,090 --> 00:16:42,110
Be polite to him.

331
00:16:47,510 --> 00:16:48,040
Mark.

332
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:50,770
-I'm here to get my cello.
-You're here.

333
00:16:52,710 --> 00:16:53,230
Hello.

334
00:16:53,660 --> 00:16:55,840
This is Xiaole, my neighbor in China.

335
00:16:55,870 --> 00:16:56,990
This is Mark.

336
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,740
Fellow townsman, huh?

337
00:16:59,580 --> 00:17:00,930
Thank you for always

338
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,160
taking care of Yi Lan.

339
00:17:07,630 --> 00:17:08,890
I'll go get your cello.

340
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:16,740
The owner
of a musical instrument store again, huh?

341
00:17:16,829 --> 00:17:17,829
Here. Take a look.

342
00:17:18,589 --> 00:17:19,790
Perfectly restored.

343
00:17:22,380 --> 00:17:24,190
There really is no trace left.

344
00:17:24,329 --> 00:17:25,400
I'm an experienced craftsman.

345
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,180
You can trust my skills.

346
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:27,180
That impressive?

347
00:17:27,660 --> 00:17:29,090
I'll transfer the money to you now.

348
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:30,490
I told you, no need to pay.

349
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:32,200
I must pay you.

350
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,000
I must pay you.

351
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:34,550
Do you have enough pocket money?

352
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:35,200
If not,

353
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:35,920
just keep it for now.

354
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:36,770
More than enough.

355
00:17:36,770 --> 00:17:37,920
I've been working part-time recently,

356
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,920
and I've made a good amount of money.

357
00:17:40,430 --> 00:17:41,960
Then shouldn't you treat me to a meal?

358
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:42,520
Sure.

359
00:17:42,590 --> 00:17:43,590
How about...

360
00:17:43,610 --> 00:17:44,290
tonight?

361
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,470
Tonight works.

362
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:47,830
After work,

363
00:17:47,870 --> 00:17:49,120
I'll come find you when I'm free.

364
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:49,920
It's a deal then.

365
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:50,500
Mm.

366
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:51,640
Yi Lan.

367
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,530
It's about time.

368
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:54,770
We should get going.

369
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,630
I still have work later.

370
00:17:56,830 --> 00:17:58,350
How about I leave the cello here for now,

371
00:17:58,350 --> 00:18:00,080
and you bring it to me at dinner?

372
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:01,040
See you tonight.

373
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,090
See you tonight.

374
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:02,690
Let's go.

375
00:18:05,850 --> 00:18:07,710
Work might run very late tonight.

376
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:09,350
Making him wait
until the middle of the night—

377
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:10,680
it's not proper, right?

378
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:13,820
What's your relationship with him?

379
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,020
He's the owner.

380
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,100
I'm his client.

381
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:21,000
Then this owner must be very successful.

382
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,200
He not only made money off you,

383
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:24,260
but also got you to treat him to a meal.

384
00:18:24,870 --> 00:18:26,240
Businessman.

385
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:32,790
♪ The story begins with hand in hand ♪

386
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:36,150
♪ For no reason at all ♪

387
00:18:36,390 --> 00:18:39,000
♪ I just want to walk with you ♪

388
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,070
Let's go.

389
00:18:40,230 --> 00:18:44,100
♪ Simply until we grow old ♪

390
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:48,980
♪ Every warm touch that drew us closer ♪

391
00:18:49,650 --> 00:18:51,740
♪ Was nothing but a dream ♪

392
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:55,580
♪ So many sunrises and sunsets ♪

393
00:18:55,870 --> 00:18:59,700
♪ Have changed our original hearts ♪

394
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:03,550
♪ By not thinking about it or guessing ♪

395
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:06,870
♪ I thought I could break free ♪

396
00:19:07,020 --> 00:19:13,980
♪ Time has shown
I'm not as carefree as I imagined ♪

397
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:19,560
♪ I still can't forget the tenderness
you gave me that year ♪

398
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:23,230
♪ Exhausting all my strength,
I still can't fool myself ♪

399
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:26,790
♪ Your place is still here ♪

400
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:27,310
How much longer
are you going to keep taking pictures?

401
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:30,710
♪ No one else can take it ♪

402
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,480
Until early tomorrow morning.

403
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:31,600
I'm going back.

404
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:32,940
The final payment.

405
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,890
Get the card holder from my bag.

406
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,440
I bought this for you.

407
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:56,100
This card holder is so worn out.

408
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,330
You're so rich.

409
00:19:57,350 --> 00:19:57,790
Why haven't you...

410
00:19:57,790 --> 00:19:59,250
replaced it with a new one?

411
00:20:00,510 --> 00:20:01,770
None of your business.

412
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:05,730
Put it back.

413
00:20:06,110 --> 00:20:07,090
You don't need it?

414
00:20:07,090 --> 00:20:08,200
I just wanted to know

415
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,400
if it was still there.

416
00:20:22,270 --> 00:20:24,400
Where are we taking pictures tonight?

417
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:25,780
You'll know soon.

418
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,060
You're hungry?

419
00:20:32,270 --> 00:20:33,600
I haven't eaten all day.

420
00:20:33,830 --> 00:20:35,290
Did I stop you from eating?

421
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:39,410
I didn't want to eat myself.

422
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:46,080
So slow.

423
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:47,830
What's so slow?

424
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,420
Xiaole?

425
00:20:55,030 --> 00:20:56,000
Mr. Chen.

426
00:20:56,550 --> 00:20:58,680
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

427
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:00,720
Chen Fan.

428
00:21:00,750 --> 00:21:01,550
Where is Ning?

429
00:21:02,030 --> 00:21:02,860
She went to rehearsal.

430
00:21:02,860 --> 00:21:03,920
She'll come later.

431
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:06,910
Why are you two together?

432
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,160
Did you get back together?

433
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,350
How is that possible?

434
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:10,940
We're in a client relationship now.

435
00:21:10,940 --> 00:21:11,920
I'm his local guide.

436
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:12,880
Local guide?

437
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,530
Where should we eat?

438
00:21:17,390 --> 00:21:18,870
I happen to know

439
00:21:18,890 --> 00:21:20,110
a star-rated restaurant.

440
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:20,890
My treat.

441
00:21:21,310 --> 00:21:22,400
So extravagant?

442
00:21:23,110 --> 00:21:25,240
Tong Xiaole is a big photographer now.

443
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:26,180
He's very rich.

444
00:21:27,830 --> 00:21:29,360
I'll go pay the parking fee.

445
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:34,670
Any progress?

446
00:21:35,430 --> 00:21:36,590
What progress could there be?

447
00:21:36,590 --> 00:21:37,610
Look at her.

448
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:38,920
Is there any hope?

449
00:21:40,550 --> 00:21:43,210
If there's no hope,
just switch to someone else.

450
00:21:45,550 --> 00:21:46,380
Say

451
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:47,820
more things like that.

452
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,400
I love hearing it.

453
00:21:58,110 --> 00:22:00,240
The wine here is pretty good, isn't it?

454
00:22:02,140 --> 00:22:04,390
This is the bar where I used to work.

455
00:22:04,410 --> 00:22:07,070
It's not a star-rated restaurant.

456
00:22:08,740 --> 00:22:10,410
You used to work here?

457
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:12,830
Whether it's a star-rated bar

458
00:22:12,830 --> 00:22:13,310
or a star-rated restaurant,

459
00:22:13,310 --> 00:22:13,820
they're both star-rated.

460
00:22:13,820 --> 00:22:15,480
They are pretty much the same.

461
00:22:16,550 --> 00:22:17,880
Xiaole, you came today.

462
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:18,210
Okay.

463
00:22:18,230 --> 00:22:19,830
You guys talk. You guys talk.

464
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:21,650
You...

465
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:24,100
You know my boss?

466
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:26,530
How did you know him?

467
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,310
That is...

468
00:22:29,330 --> 00:22:31,290
a long story.

469
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:33,930
So what are we eating today?

470
00:22:41,310 --> 00:22:42,110
So?

471
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,470
You usually...

472
00:22:44,350 --> 00:22:46,410
don't get to eat these dishes abroad.

473
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:49,960
Ning, here.

474
00:22:50,590 --> 00:22:51,440
Luo Ningzi.

475
00:22:52,030 --> 00:22:52,960
Long time no see.

476
00:22:55,010 --> 00:22:55,480
Sir,

477
00:22:55,690 --> 00:22:56,740
another dozen beers.

478
00:22:56,740 --> 00:22:57,410
Okay.

479
00:22:58,590 --> 00:23:01,640
We should drink to our heart's content
on a day like this.

480
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,900
You still can hold your liquor well, huh?

481
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,800
I heard in the orchestra, you...

482
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:16,910
I didn't say anything.

483
00:23:18,550 --> 00:23:20,150
Life is tough abroad, right?

484
00:23:20,410 --> 00:23:21,680
Tong Xiaole, that mouth of yours

485
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:22,590
hasn't changed a bit.

486
00:23:22,590 --> 00:23:23,640
If you weren't treating,

487
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:25,040
no one would eat with you.

488
00:23:25,110 --> 00:23:26,270
You're asking for a beating.

489
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:27,240
I'm just showing concern.

490
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:27,840
It's okay.

491
00:23:28,410 --> 00:23:29,660
It indeed is tough.

492
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:31,850
I don't even want to stay here anymore.

493
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:33,170
You don't want to stay here?

494
00:23:33,170 --> 00:23:34,370
You don't want to stay here?

495
00:23:34,370 --> 00:23:35,400
Ning, regarding this,

496
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,780
you shouldn't be impulsive.

497
00:23:36,780 --> 00:23:38,750
I think you should reconsider carefully.

498
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:39,270
How about this?

499
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:39,920
Let's talk about it

500
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:41,580
after... we wake up tomorrow.

501
00:23:42,570 --> 00:23:43,570
I don't think

502
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,680
there's anything wrong with that idea.

503
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:45,780
Since it's so hard abroad,

504
00:23:45,780 --> 00:23:47,640
she might as well go back to China.

505
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:48,350
After she returns to China,

506
00:23:48,350 --> 00:23:50,210
you can form an orchestra for her.

507
00:23:51,550 --> 00:23:52,700
You two truly are a pair.

508
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:54,500
You even sound exactly the same.

509
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,560
What's the big deal?

510
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,600
Anyone could think of that.

511
00:23:58,810 --> 00:23:59,840
Eat. Eat.

512
00:24:13,550 --> 00:24:14,350
Xiaole.

513
00:24:15,550 --> 00:24:16,830
Are you in a relationship again?

514
00:24:16,830 --> 00:24:18,570
What... What do you mean "again"?

515
00:24:18,570 --> 00:24:20,170
Since... Since I broke up...

516
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:21,310
Since I broke up with her,

517
00:24:21,310 --> 00:24:22,970
I haven't dated anyone, okay?

518
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:25,610
Xiaole is right.

519
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:26,880
He's so busy with work.

520
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:29,210
How would he have time for a relationship?

521
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:31,120
Don't worry. Don't worry.

522
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:32,270
Don't worry. Don't worry.

523
00:24:32,270 --> 00:24:34,350
Why... Why would I be worried?

524
00:24:34,510 --> 00:24:37,510
Whether you're single or not
has nothing to do with me.

525
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:40,680
We haven't seen each other for so long.

526
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:41,640
After we finish eating,

527
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:43,240
should we go somewhere to take a walk

528
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:43,970
and hang out?

529
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:45,130
Sure.

530
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,460
With this weather,

531
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:48,880
drinking outside is the most comfortable.

532
00:24:49,830 --> 00:24:51,290
Sir, another dozen beers!

533
00:24:52,070 --> 00:24:54,070
You're indulging her this much now?

534
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:56,180
It's not like
she drinks like this every day.

535
00:24:56,180 --> 00:24:57,270
She's happy today,

536
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:58,760
so let her drink a bit more.

537
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,110
You just keep spoiling her.

538
00:25:00,110 --> 00:25:01,580
Then you're paying

539
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:02,550
for the beers later.

540
00:25:02,550 --> 00:25:03,310
So stingy.

541
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:04,720
So

542
00:25:04,790 --> 00:25:05,400
stingy.

543
00:25:05,590 --> 00:25:06,840
I don't have much money right now.

544
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:07,510
Yi Lan said I'm rich,

545
00:25:07,510 --> 00:25:09,170
and you actually believed it?

546
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:15,810
Let's drink a toast.

547
00:25:19,510 --> 00:25:21,240
The weather is quite pleasant.

548
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:24,200
So,

549
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:27,410
how does it feel
to become a big photographer?

550
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,680
I've won some popularity,

551
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:33,480
but I still have no money.

552
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:35,610
I even have to carry beers for someone.

553
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:41,030
You always go to such dangerous places
to take photos.

554
00:25:41,030 --> 00:25:42,090
Aren't you afraid?

555
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,770
What if you can't come back?

556
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:44,660
I am afraid.

557
00:25:46,350 --> 00:25:48,210
But if I really can't come back...

558
00:25:49,070 --> 00:25:50,070
so be it.

559
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:54,260
What about you two?

560
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,200
How long have you been together?

561
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:59,260
Six years and one month.

562
00:25:59,450 --> 00:26:00,410
Isn't it 7 years?

563
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:02,310
Didn't we

564
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:04,090
break up for nearly half a year?

565
00:26:04,510 --> 00:26:04,770
Yeah.

566
00:26:04,770 --> 00:26:05,300
I forgot.

567
00:26:07,310 --> 00:26:09,170
You've been together for so long.

568
00:26:09,430 --> 00:26:10,630
Do you have any plans?

569
00:26:13,030 --> 00:26:14,030
We plan...

570
00:26:14,460 --> 00:26:15,420
to get married.

571
00:26:16,570 --> 00:26:17,660
Get married?

572
00:26:17,750 --> 00:26:18,660
You wish.

573
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:19,530
You get married yourself.

574
00:26:19,530 --> 00:26:21,330
You and Tong Xiaole get married.

575
00:26:26,540 --> 00:26:27,700
What about you two?

576
00:26:30,270 --> 00:26:32,230
You've known each other for so long.

577
00:26:32,230 --> 00:26:33,480
Whatever the issue is,

578
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:34,790
just talk it out.

579
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:38,880
It's quite cold.

580
00:26:38,990 --> 00:26:40,560
Why don't we go inside
and sit for a while?

581
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:42,090
There are seats over there.

582
00:26:43,750 --> 00:26:44,420
It's all your fault.

583
00:26:44,420 --> 00:26:46,220
Why did you have to bring that up?

584
00:26:47,310 --> 00:26:48,570
Lan, I'm coming!

585
00:26:49,550 --> 00:26:51,150
I didn't say anything wrong.

586
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:53,040
You didn't. Let's go.

587
00:26:56,250 --> 00:26:57,620
Have some snacks.

588
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:10,810
You can eat over there.

589
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,040
I want to eat all of these.

590
00:27:22,150 --> 00:27:23,410
Then sit here.

591
00:27:23,780 --> 00:27:24,680
Okay.

592
00:27:31,070 --> 00:27:31,830
Yes, My Lady.

593
00:27:31,850 --> 00:27:33,380
I'll go buy them right away.

594
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:34,390
Xiaole,

595
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:35,610
come with me.

596
00:27:36,390 --> 00:27:37,160
To buy beers.

597
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:38,360
I'm not going.

598
00:27:39,290 --> 00:27:40,130
Come on!

599
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:41,440
I'm eating pastries!

600
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:42,030
Come on!

601
00:27:42,310 --> 00:27:42,640
Hey.

602
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,000
Lan,

603
00:27:50,610 --> 00:27:52,680
will you and Tong Xiaole
get back together?
